Brazil Broadband Plan to Increase Internet Speed, Folha Says

-- B y   F a b i o l a   M o u r a
-- 
2011-04-10T15:11:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-10/brazil-broadband-plan-to-increase-internet-speed-folha-says.html
Brazil  increased to one megabit per
second the minimum speed in its plan to extend broadband
Internet services to all homes,  Folha de Sao Paulo  newspaper
reported, without saying how it got the information.  The new requirement will allow for better service and may
delay the beginning of the program for as many as three months,
Folha reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fabiola Moura in New York at 
 fdemoura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at 
 swier@bloomberg.net  